==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Walk-over
<hw>Walk"-o`ver</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>In racing, the
going over a course by a horse which has no competitor for the
prize.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <mark>(colloquially)</mark>
<def>A one-sided contest; an uncontested, or an easy, victory.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> walk; cake-walk.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Walkyr</ent>⟦br⟧
